-- Mets Beat Pirates 3-2 on Baxter’s Run Scoring Single in Ninth
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-05-10T04:57:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-10/mets-beat-pirates-3-2-on-baxter-s-run-scoring-single-in-ninth.html
Mike Baxter hit a run-scoring single
in the ninth inning to give the New York Mets a 3-2 victory over
the Pittsburgh Pirates.  Bobby Parnell (4-0) allowed one hit and struck out one in
the ninth inning last night as the Mets improved to 14 wins and
17 losses in Major League Baseball.  John Buck scored on Marlon Byrd’s sacrifice fly in the
second inning to give the Mets a 1-0 lead before Andrew McCutchen tied the game in the sixth on Pedro Alvarez’s
sacrifice fly at Citi field.  Ike Davis’s run-scoring double in the seventh made it 2-1
to New York and Alvarez hit a home run in the eighth to tie the
game again before Baxter came in as a pinch-hitter.  Jason Grilli (0-1) surrendered one run on two hits in one-third innings for the Loss for the Pirates (18-16).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
